---
import BaseHead from "../components/BaseHead.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ColorScript from "../components/ColorScript.astro";
import { SITE_TITLE } from "../config";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en-us">
	<BaseHead title={`About 路 ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="AI/ML Consultant specializing in Generative AI and Large Language Models for Enterprise Solutions" />
	<body>
		<Header title={SITE_TITLE} />
		<main>
			<article class="about-page">
				<header class="page-header">
					<h1>Syed Asad Zaman</h1>
					<p class="subtitle">AI/ML Consultant 路 IBM Consulting 路 Islamabad, Pakistan</p>
				</header>

				<section class="intro-block">
					<h2 class="hook-title">The Problem That Changed Everything</h2>
					<p>
						At 3 AM, I was staring at server logs, trying to diagnose why a critical database was bleeding performance. 
						Hours of manual analysis, digging through AWR reports, correlating metrics across systems. I thought: 
						&quot;There has to be a better way.&quot;
					</p>
					<p>
						That frustration led me to build DB HealthWatch&mdash;a GenAI assistant that now diagnoses database issues 
						in minutes instead of hours. It&apos;s the kind of problem-solving that excites me: taking painful, manual 
						processes and transforming them with intelligent automation.
					</p>
					<p>
						I&apos;m a Computer Scientist and AI Engineer who turns complex enterprise problems into elegant AI solutions. 
						Over the past three years at IBM Consulting, I&apos;ve built production systems that process thousands of daily 
						requests across healthcare, telecommunications, and enterprise infrastructure&mdash;proving that the real value 
						of AI isn&apos;t in the hype, it&apos;s in solving actual business problems.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="section-block">
					<h2>What I Build</h2>
					<p class="philosophy">
						I&apos;m obsessed with taking painful manual processes and automating them with AI. Not because it&apos;s trendy, 
						but because I&apos;ve been the person staying up at 3 AM manually diagnosing issues that should&apos;ve been 
						automated years ago.
					</p>
					<p class="philosophy">
						The best AI solutions are boring. They don&apos;t sound like sci-fi. They just quietly save people hours 
						of tedious work every single day.
					</p>
					<p class="philosophy">
						Here&apos;s what that philosophy looks like in practice:
					</p>

					<div class="project-highlight">
						<h3>DB HealthWatch</h3>
						<p>
							GenAI-powered assistant for intelligent database diagnostics. Remember that 3 AM problem? 
							Here&apos;s what I built to solve it.
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Natural language interface: &quot;Why is query performance degraded?&quot; leads to automated AWR analysis</li>
							<li>Proactive alerting system with severity classification (Good/Warning/Critical)</li>
							<li><strong>60% reduction</strong> in average diagnosis time (5 hours to 2 hours)</li>
							<li><strong>35% faster</strong> incident response across 50+ production databases</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="tech-stack">Python 路 LangChain 路 GPT-4 路 FAISS 路 RAG</p>
						<p class="impact">The Impact: DBAs can now focus on optimization instead of diagnosis</p>
					</div>

					<div class="project-highlight">
						<h3>XM Support</h3>
						<p>
							24/7 customer experience automation&mdash;built for a client drowning in repetitive support tickets.
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Automated responses to 120+ common queries</li>
							<li><strong>40% ticket reduction</strong> (from 200 to 120 per week)</li>
							<li>Sub-2-second response times with Pinecone vector search</li>
							<li>Customer satisfaction jumped from 3.2 to 4.5 stars</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="tech-stack">Python 路 FastAPI 路 LangChain 路 OpenAI GPT-4 路 Pinecone 路 Streamlit</p>
						<p class="impact">The Learning: Good prompt engineering beats complex architectures for most use cases</p>
					</div>

					<div class="project-highlight">
						<h3>MediCare.AI</h3>
						<p>
							Healthcare has terrible UX. We fixed appointment management with conversational AI.
						</p>
						<ul>
							<li>Patients book appointments, check results, find doctors&mdash;all through conversational AI</li>
							<li><strong>60% reduction</strong> in clinic admin workload (15 hours/week to 6 hours/week)</li>
							<li>Handles 200+ patient interactions daily with 94% accuracy</li>
							<li>Multi-agent orchestration using LangGraph for complex workflows</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="tech-stack">Python 路 LangGraph 路 LangChain 路 Vector Databases</p>
						<p class="impact">The Challenge: Healthcare data is messy. RAG architecture saved us.</p>
					</div>

					<p class="cta">
						Want to see the code? Check out my <a href="/projects">projects page</a> or 
						<a href="https://github.com/essayyzed" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
					</p>
				</section>

				<section class="section-block">
					<h2>How I Got Here</h2>
					
					<div class="journey-item">
						<div class="journey-header">
							<h3>IBM Consulting</h3>
							<span class="timeline">Feb 2023 - Present (2 years 10 months)</span>
						</div>
						<p>
							Currently wearing multiple hats: AI Engineer building GenAI platforms, Maximo Consultant implementing 
							enterprise asset management, and former Package Consultant supporting Vodafone&apos;s CVM ecosystem. 
							Led projects across database diagnostics, customer experience automation, and healthcare workflows.
						</p>
						<p class="lesson">
							<strong>What I Learned</strong> Production systems teach you things no tutorial ever will. The gap 
							between &quot;it works on my machine&quot; and &quot;it scales to 10K users&quot; is where real engineering happens.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="journey-item">
						<div class="journey-header">
							<h3>COLAB @ FAST NUCES</h3>
							<span class="timeline">Jun 2021 - Jul 2022 (Peshawar)</span>
						</div>
						<p>
							Led a 30-person research team under Dr. Mohammad Nauman. Managed hiring, training, and roadmap development. 
							This wasn&apos;t just research&mdash;it was where I learned to present, teach, and lead. Weekly presentations to 100+ 
							students forced me to get good at explaining complex ideas simply.
						</p>
						<p class="lesson">
							<strong>What I Learned</strong> Communication matters as much as code. The best technical solution 
							is worthless if you can&apos;t convince anyone to use it. <a href="/posts/how-colab-transformed-my-journey">Read the full story</a>
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="journey-item">
						<div class="journey-header">
							<h3>FAST NUCES</h3>
							<span class="timeline">2018 - 2022 (BS Computer Science)</span>
						</div>
						<p>
							Final year project: <strong>HyperDrive</strong>&mdash;autonomous navigation using Deep Reinforcement Learning in CARLA. 
							Used DQN, DDQN, and D* Search. It crashed into virtual walls a lot, but I learned how to debug RL agents.
						</p>
						<p>
							Research: Attribute Division using Three Way Decisions for Differential Privacy (ORIC funded). 
							My introduction to the gap between academic ML and production reality.
						</p>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section-block">
					<h2>What I Believe</h2>
					
					<div class="belief-item">
						<h3>On RAG vs Fine-Tuning</h3>
						<p>
							For 90% of enterprise use cases, RAG wins. It&apos;s cheaper, faster to iterate, and doesn&apos;t require 
							retraining when your data changes. Fine-tuning is powerful, but most companies don&apos;t need it.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="belief-item">
						<h3>On AI Hype</h3>
						<p>
							The best AI solutions are boring. They automate tedious tasks, reduce manual work, and save time. 
							If your AI project sounds like sci-fi, it&apos;s probably not solving a real problem.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="belief-item">
						<h3>On Production Systems</h3>
						<p>
							A working system that solves 80% of the problem is worth more than a perfect system that never ships. 
							Ship fast, iterate, learn from users. Production teaches you humility.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div class="belief-item">
						<h3>On Learning</h3>
						<p>
							I learned more debugging production issues at 2 AM than I did in 4 years of university. Theory matters, 
							but there&apos;s no substitute for building things that break and figuring out why.
						</p>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="section-block">
					<h2>What I Know</h2>
					
					<div class="skills-compact">
						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>Building Production LLM Systems:</strong> 
							3 systems in production serving 10K+ queries daily 路 RAG architectures (FAISS, Pinecone) 路 
							LangChain/LangGraph 路 Prompt Engineering
						</div>

						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>Core Stack:</strong> 
							Python (production code for 3+ years) 路 FastAPI 路 Streamlit 路 SQL 路 JavaScript 路 Java
						</div>

						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>Databases:</strong> 
							Oracle 路 PostgreSQL 路 MongoDB 路 Pinecone 路 FAISS 路 Supabase
						</div>

						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>AI Tools:</strong> 
							OpenAI GPT models 路 IBM watsonx.ai 路 TensorFlow 路 LangChain 路 LangGraph
						</div>

						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>Industries:</strong> 
							Telecommunications (Vodafone CVM) 路 Healthcare (MediCare.AI) 路 Enterprise IT (DB diagnostics) 路 
							Energy & Utilities (Maximo implementations)
						</div>

						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>Certifications That Matter:</strong> 
							IBM watsonx.ai Technical Essentials 路 Enterprise Design Thinking Practitioner 路 IBM Agile Explorer 路 
							Power Skills (Communication, Presentation, Collaboration)
						</div>

						<div class="skill-group">
							<strong>Languages:</strong> 
							English (Fluent) 路 Urdu (Fluent) 路 Pashto (Fluent)
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				<section class="contact-section">
					<h2>Let&apos;s Connect</h2>
					<p>
						I write about AI, production systems, and lessons learned from building things that break.
					</p>
					<p>
						<strong>Open to:</strong> Consulting opportunities, interesting AI projects, technical discussions, 
						and learning from people smarter than me.
					</p>
					<p class="not-interested">
						<strong>Not interested in:</strong> Blockchain AI NFT metaverse projects (unless you&apos;re joking, then I&apos;m in).
					</p>
					<div class="contact-links">
						<a href="mailto:essayyzed@gmail.com"> essayyzed@gmail.com</a>
						<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/essayyzed/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> LinkedIn</a>
						<a href="https://github.com/essayyzed" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> GitHub</a>
						<a href="https://twitter.com/essayyzed" target="_blank" rel="noopener"> Twitter</a>
					</div>
				</section>
			</article>
		</main>
		<Footer />
		<ColorScript />
	</body>
</html>

